ot%3B%20Modi%20reciprocated%20by%20highlighting%20the%20special%20nature%20of%20this%20visit%3A%20%26quot%3BBecause%20she%20is%20our%20first%20state%20guest%20after%20our%20government%20returned%20to%20power%20for%20the%20third%20term.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Funilateral-discussions-mamata-banerjee-to-pm-on-bangladesh-talks-5959096%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%26quot%3BUnilateral%20Discussions...%26quot%3B%3A%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20To%20PM%20On%20Bangladesh%20Talks%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20visit%20saw%20the%20signing%20of%2010%20Memoranda%20of%20Understanding%20(MoUs)%2C%20which%20covered%20areas%20as%20diverse%20as%20digital%20and%20green%20partnerships%2C%20maritime%20cooperation%2C%20and%2C%20notably%2C%20the%20'Shared%20Vision%20for%20India-Bangladesh%20Rail%20Connectivity'.%20The%20joint%20statement%20outlined%20a%20shared%20bilateral%20and%20regional%20vision%20for%20peace%2C%20prosperity%20and%20development%2C%20driven%20by%20connectivity%2C%20commerce%20and%20collaboration.%20In%20that%20spirit%2C%20some%20important%20new%20initiatives%20were%20announced%2C%20including%20e-visa%20for%20patients%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20new%20train%20and%20bus%20services%2C%20joint%20technical%20committee%20for%20Ganga%20Water%20Treaty%2C%20visit%20of%20an%20Indian%20technical%20team%20to%20Bangladesh%20for%20a%20mega%20project%20to%20conserve%20and%20manage%20the%20Teesta%20river%2C%20export%20of%2040%20MW%20of%20power%20from%20Nepal%20to%20Bangladesh%20through%20Indian%20grid%2C%20and%20training%20of%20Bangladeshi%20police%20officers.%20Building%20Bangladesh's%20defence%20capability%20has%20also%20emerged%20as%20a%20priority%2C%20with%20the%20two%20nations%20deciding%20%26quot%3Bto%20explore%20defence%20industrial%20cooperation%20for%20modernisation%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20of%20Bangladesh%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIdentifying%20Opportunities%2C%20Counterbalancing%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20will%20be%20visiting%20China%20in%20July.%20It%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20new%20maturity%20in%20India-Bangladesh%20relations%20that%20the%20two%20nations%20continue%20to%20work%20closely%20together%20even%20as%20they%20develop%20their%20ties%20with%20other%20nations.%20New%20Delhi%20has%20not%20stopped%20Dhaka%20from%20its%20engagement%20with%20China%20but%20it%20has%20some%20concerns%20that%20Hasina%20has%20always%20ensured%20are%20addressed.%20Since%202020%2C%20China%20has%20been%20regularly%20expressing%20an%20interest%20in%20the%20%241%20billion%20project%20to%20develop%20the%20Teesta%20river.%20Last%20year%2C%20Beijing%20submitted%20a%20formal%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftripura-chief-minister-gifts-500-kg-of-queen-pineapples-to-bangladesh-pm-5952493%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0Tripura%20Chief%20Minister%20Gifts%20500%20Kg%20Of%20Queen%20Pineapples%20To%20Bangladesh%20PM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Bangladesh%2C%20this%20has%20been%20a%20long-standing%20priority.%20The%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%20had%20an%20agreement%20in%20place%20in%202011%2C%20which%20could%20not%20be%20taken%20forward%20due%20to%20the%20opposition%20from%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20West%20Bengal.%20For%20Hasina%2C%20the%20situation%20had%20become%20unsustainable%2C%20with%20the%20opposition%20clamouring%20for%20a%20response%20amidst%20moves%20by%20the%20Chinese.%20Her%20visit%20before%20going%20to%20China%20was%20a%20wise%20move%20to%20ensure%20that%20New%20Delhi%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20respond%2C%20and%20India%20has%20done%20well%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20initiative.%20The%20decision%20to%20send%20an%20Indian%20technical%20team%20to%20Dhaka%20for%20talks%20on%20the%20conservation%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-bangladesh-agree-on-mega-project-to-conserve-teesta-river-5947924%5C%22%3Emanagement%20of%20Teesta%20river%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20indication%20that%20New%20Delhi%20is%20not%20willing%20to%20cede%20its%20strategic%20space%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20despite%20domestic%20challenges.%20The%20decision%20to%20commence%20technical%20negotiations%20for%20the%20renewal%20of%20the%201996%20Ganga%20Water%20Treaty%20is%20also%20a%20timely%20move%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20concerns%20in%20Dhaka%20on%20an%20issue%20that%20is%20a%20priority%20for%20the%20Hasina%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERock-Solid%20Ties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20Bangladesh%20cannot%20be%20overstated%20as%20New%20Delhi%20seeks%20to%20emerge%20as%20an%20Indo-Pacific%20player%20with%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20as%20the%20regional%20epicentre.%20For%20Bangladesh%2C%20a%20partnership%20with%20India%20remains%20key%20to%20realising%20its%20full%20potential%20as%20a%20critical%20economic%20and%20strategic%20player%20in%20the%20region.%20As%20the%20two%20nations%20become%20more%20ambitious%20in%20defining%20their%20strategic%20outlooks%2C%20their%20bilateral%20partnership%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20key%20enabler%20in%20shaping%20their%20behaviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20China%20factor%2C%20while%20important%2C%20should%20not%20be%20overstated.%20India-Bangladesh%20ties%20today%20stand%20on%20their%20own%20merit.%20Hasina%20and%20Modi%20have%20ensured%20that%20by%20focusing%20concrete%20tangible%20outcomes%20for%20the%20people%20of%20both%20nations%2C%20they%20have%20redefined%20the%20contours%20of%20what%20an%20ideal%20partnership%20between%20two%20neighbours%20should%20look%20like.%20Mutual%20respect%2C%20mutual%20interest%20and%20mutual%20sensitivity%20have%20made%20this%20relationship%20an%20exemplar%20for%20all%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BHarsh%20V%20Pant%20is%20Vice%20President%20for%20Studies%20and%20Foreign%20Policy%20at%20ORF.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719234600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F73t1hnb8_sheikh-hasina_625x300_22_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmodi-hasina-should-worry-about-china-but-not-too-much-5959266%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20China%20factor%2C%20while%20important%2C%20should%20not%20be%20overstated.%20India-Bangladesh%20ties%20today%20stand%20on%20their%20own%20merit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmodi-hasina-should-worry-about-china-but-not-too-much-5959266%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmodi-hasina-should-worry-about-china-but-not-too-much-5959266%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmodi-hasina-should-worry-about-china-but-not-too-much-5959266%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Lok%20Sabha%3A%20How%20Past%20Coalition%20Governments%20Have%20Elected%20Speakers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fhfb3nes_parliament_625x300_07_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20soon%20choose%20a%20new%20Speaker.%20Given%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)-led%20coalition%20government%20in%20power%2C%20with%20the%20ruling%20party%20just%20shy%20of%20a%20majority%20on%20its%20own%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20Speaker%20has%20drawn%20considerable%20attention.%20The%20office%20has%20been%20the%20focus%20of%20attention%20especially%20when%20ruling%20parties%2Falliances%20have%20slimmer%20majorities%20and%20splits%20in%20parties%20become%20the%20order%20of%20the%20day.%20The%20Speaker%20has%20a%20vital%20role%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20interpreting%20anti-defection%20provisions%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20presiding%20over%20what%20can%20often%20be%20an%20acrimonious%20house%20on%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20around%2C%20there%20was%20initial%20talk%20of%20members%20of%20the%20non-BJP%2C%20NDA%20(National%20Democratic%20Alliance)%20coalition%20partners%20seeking%20the%20Speaker's%20post.%20This%20rumour%20gradually%20receded%20with%20the%20principal%20non-BJP%20parties%20in%20the%20coalition%20conceding%20that%20it%20should%20be%20left%20to%20the%20BJP%20to%20have%20a%20candidate%20of%20its%20choice.%20There%20are%20reports%20of%20a%20formal%20process%20of%20consultation%20being%20initiated%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20this%20regard.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIt%20is%20important%20to%20record%20that%20whenever%20a%20party%20has%20secured%20a%20clear%20majority%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Speaker%20has%20always%20been%20from%20the%20ruling%20party.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20slightly%20different%20story%20whenever%20we%20have%20had%20coalition%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Rabi%20Ray%20To%20P.A.%20Sangma%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201989%2C%20Rabi%20Ray%20from%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20became%20the%20Speaker%20as%20the%20National%20Front%20government%20led%20by%20V.P.%20Singh%20assumed%20office.%20In%201991%2C%20when%20the%20Congress%20formed%20a%20minority%20government%2C%20Shivraj%20Patil%20from%20the%20Congress%20became%20Speaker.%20In%201998%2C%20when%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20came%20to%20power%2C%20Balayogi%20from%20the%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20Speaker%2C%20and%20he%20was%20re-elected%20in%201999.%20Later%2C%20when%20he%20passed%20away%2C%20the%20post%20went%20to%20another%20BJP%20ally%20in%20the%20NDA%3A%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20with%20Manohar%20Joshi%20becoming%20speaker.%20When%20the%20UPA%20came%20to%20power%20in%202004%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20which%20was%20an%20ally%2C%20saw%20its%20leader%20Somnath%20Chatterjee%20becoming%20the%20Speaker.%20In%202009%2C%20the%20second%20UPA%20government%20saw%20Meira%20Kumar%20from%20the%20Congress%20being%20elected%20as%20the%20Speaker.%3Cbr%3E%5CnDuring%20the%20first%20two%20BJP-led%20NDA%20governments%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20Sumitra%20Mahajan%20and%20Om%20Birla%20held%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20time%20when%20the%20Speaker%20did%20not%20hail%20from%20a%20party%20or%20alliance%20which%20came%20to%20power%20after%20the%20election%20was%201996.%20This%20was%20on%20account%20of%20the%20unique%20political%20circumstances%20that%20prevailed%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Speaker's%20election.%20No%20party%20had%20secured%20a%20majority%20in%20the%20election%20and%20the%20President%20had%20invited%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20to%20form%20the%20government.%20The%20Vajpayee%20government%20did%20not%20have%20a%20majority%20and%20was%20not%20keen%20on%20a%20floor%20test%20before%20moving%20the%20confidence%20motion.%20The%20Speaker's%20election%20came%20first.%20The%20Opposition%20decided%20to%20field%20P.A.%20Sangma%20for%20the%20post%20of%20Speaker.%20In%20a%20strategic%20move%2C%20the%20BJP%20decided%20not%20to%20field%20a%20candidate%20and%20went%20on%20to%20state%20that%20Sangma%20was%20endorsed%20by%20them%20too.%20The%20Opposition%20candidate%20was%20thus%20unanimously%20elected%20as%20Speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20UK%20Does%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20record%20that%20in%20the%20home%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20there%20is%20a%20convention%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20that%20once%20someone%20is%20elected%20as%20Speaker%2C%20he%20or%20she%20gives%20up%20membership%20of%20his%2Fher%20party.%20No%20party%20puts%20up%20a%20candidate%20against%20the%20speaker%20in%20the%20next%20elections%20and%20they%20continue%20as%20speaker%20till%20they%20decide%20to%20retire.%20This%20explains%20the%20adage%20%60Once%20a%20Speaker.%20Always%20a%20Speaker!'.%20In%20his%20famous%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EFirst%20Among%20Equals%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Jeffrey%20Archer%20has%20a%20character%20who%20competes%20for%20the%20position%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20majority%20party.%20When%20he%20loses%2C%20he%20decides%20to%20retire%20from%20active%20politics%20and%20becomes%20Speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20mentioned%20above%20has%20not%20been%20followed%20in%20India.%20Speakers%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20become%20Union%20Ministers.%20Gurdial%20Singh%20Dhillon%2C%20Shivraj%20Patil%20and%20Balram%20Jakhar%20can%20be%20cited%20as%20examples%20in%20this%20regard.%20N.%20Sanjiva%20Reddy%20resigned%20on%20two%20different%20occasions%20(1969%20and%201977)%20as%20Speaker%20in%20order%20to%20contest%20the%20Presidential%20elections.%20He%20lost%20the%20first%20time%20and%20won%20the%20next%20time.%20It%20is%20also%20important%20to%20note%20that%20four%20Speakers%20lost%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20after%20completing%20their%20term%20as%20speaker.%20These%20include%20Baliram%20Bhagat%20(1977)%2C%20Balram%20Jakhar%20(1989)%2C%20Manohar%20Joshi%20(2004)%20and%20Meira%20Kumar%20(2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20few%20days%2C%20who%20becomes%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20be%20clear.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20given%20the%20party's%20dominance%20in%20the%20NDA%2C%20the%20BJP%20will%20be%20able%20to%20ensure%20that%20its%20nominee%20occupies%20the%20presiding%20officer's%20chair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Dr.%20Sandeep%20Shastri%20is%20the%20National%20Coordinator%20of%20the%20Lokniti%20Network)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719234420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fhfb3nes_parliament_625x300_07_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-various-coalition-governments-have-elected-speakers-5959889%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Whenever%20a%20party%20has%20secured%20a%20clear%20majority%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Speaker%20has%20always%20been%20from%20the%20ruling%20party.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20slightly%20different%20story%20whenever%20we%20have%20had%20coalition%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-various-coalition-governments-have-elected-speakers-5959889%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-various-coalition-governments-have-elected-speakers-5959889%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-various-coalition-governments-have-elected-speakers-5959889%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Student%20Who%20Cleared%20NEET%20Doesn't%20Want%20A%20Re-Test.%20Here's%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20around%20National%20Eligibility%20cum%20Entrance%20Test%20(NEET)%20for%20medical%20admissions%20has%20come%20as%20a%20shock%20to%20those%20students%20who%20have%20secured%20good%20marks.%20One%20such%20aspirant%20is%20Kartikeya%20Gupta%20from%20Lucknow.%20He%20secured%20685%20marks%20out%20of%20720%2C%20and%20was%20hoping%20to%20get%20into%20a%20good%20college.%20But%20with%20coaching%20institutes%2C%20parents%20and%20some%20students%20taking%20the%20legal%20route%20and%20demanding%20the%20entrance%20exam%20to%20be%20re-conducted%2C%20the%20youngster%20is%20anxious%20about%20the%20future.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20refused%20to%20defer%20the%20counselling%20date%2C%20scheduled%20for%20July%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20disturbed%20by%20what%20has%20happened.%20When%20a%20student%20prepares%20for%20exam%2C%20he%2Fshe%20has%20a%20date%20in%20mind.%20Nobody%20cares%20about%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20that.%20Nobody%20has%20a%20backup%20plan%2C%20all%20of%20us%20trust%20the%20government%20and%20the%20entire%20system%20that%20something%20like%20this%20will%20never%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Kartikeya%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20this%20uncertainty%20a%20month%20after%20the%20exam%20is%20making%20students%20like%20me%20nervous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fneet-paper-leak-row-exams-cancelled-and-postponed-so-far-5957273%5C%22%3ENEET%20Paper%20Leak%20Row%3A%20Exams%20Cancelled%20And%20Postponed%20So%20Far%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NEET%20exam%20was%20held%20on%20May%205%20and%20results%20came%20out%20on%20June%204.%20This%20was%20Kartikeya's%20second%20attempt%20and%20his%20score%20increased%20from%20501%20to%20685%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20happy%20that%20I%20will%20at%20least%20get%20a%20good%20college.%20But%20after%20the%20entire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fdisappointing-that-students-ex-union-minister-rajeev-chandrasekhar-amid-neet-exam-row-5954934%5C%22%3ENEET%20controversy%3C%2Fa%3E%20unfolded%2C%20new%20facts%20are%20emerging%20every%20day.%20I%20am%20anxious%20and%20want%20to%20know%20what%20will%20happen%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kartikeya.%20The%20aspirant%20blamed%20students%20who%20try%20to%20pass%20by%20buying%20papers%20instead%20of%20studying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20takes%20an%20entire%20year%20to%20set%20a%20rhythm%2C%20and%20now%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20make%20it.%20Kartikeya%20said%20he%20doesn't%20want%20a%20re-test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKartikeya's%20mother%20Preeti%20Gupta%20is%20also%20angry%20with%20this%20whole%20controversy.%20She%20said%20that%20parents%20give%20their%20all%20for%20the%20education%20of%20the%20child%2C%20but%20despite%20the%20good%20results%2C%20the%20future%20of%20her%20son%20hangs%20in%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20very%20happy%20with%20his%20marks%20and%20I%20am%20urging%20the%20government%20not%20to%20cancel%20the%20exam%2C%26quot%3B%20Mrs%20Gupta%20told%20NDTV%2C%20adding%20that%20children%20have%20to%20suffer%20due%20to%20a%20flaw%20in%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20began%20after%20an%20unprecedented%2067%20candidates%20achieved%20a%20perfect%20score%20of%20720%20marks%20out%20of%20720%2C%20which%20led%20to%20protests%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20ordered%20re-conduct%20of%20the%20exam%20for%201%2C563%20students%20who%20had%20experienced%20time%20loss%20during%20the%20originally%20scheduled%20examination%20and%20received%20grace%20marks%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20testing%20Agency%20(NTA).%20The%20re-test%20happened%20on%20Monday%20but%20only%2052%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20candidates%20appeared%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20NEET%20irregularities%20allegations%2C%20the%20Centre%20postponed%20the%20NEET-PG%20exam%20a%20day%20ahead%20of%20its%20postponed%20date%20and%20cancelled%20the%20UGC-NET%20exam%20conducted%20on%20June%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fneet-exam-row-net-nta-probe-4-phase-probe-1-000-phone-numbers-cbi-plan-to-crack-paper-leak-cases-5958970%5C%22%3ECentral%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CBI)%20registered%20a%20criminal%20case%20based%20on%20a%20written%20complaint%20from%20the%20Director%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Higher%20Education%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Education%20over%20NEET%20irregularities.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719234300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F7e7cvlk_neet-exam-stud